pageContext.claim: “I mean the polls have closed in Texas. Donald Trump has won, the state of Texas. It was like all in one thing. They don't do that unless you have a landslide, so we had like, and now they do the same thing again.”
pageContext.analysis: Networks make calls in presidential races for a wide variety of reasons — not always having to do with a landslide in a given state. They can be based on early returns from populous, contentious counties as well.
